The reaction kinetics of MnHCF/NCDs and MnHCF materials were further evaluated by EIS. As shown in Fig. 6
                        d, the electrode's Nyquist plot is made up of a semicircle in the high-frequency area and a straight line in the low-frequency region. The semicircular component is connected to the charge transfer resistance (Rct
                        ) at the electrode/electrolyte interface, whereas the Warburg impedance (Wo
                        ), which is caused by the diffusion of Zn2+, is related to the linear part [48]. Using the equivalent circuit, several electrode kinetic parameters were fitted (inset of Fig. 6
                        d). MnHCF/NCDs and MnHCF have charge transfer resistances (Rct
                        ) of 10.8 and 107.6, respectively, indicating that MnHCF/NCDs performs charge transfer faster than MnHCF (Table S2). Meanwhile, Fig. S7 shows that the σw
                         of MnHCF/NCDs is 118.4, while that of MnHCF is 244.8, which indicates that the ion diffusion resistance in the composite is lower than that of MnHCF.
